

Shellcoding

Shellcode is a set of instructions that executes a command in software to take control of or exploit a compromised machine. 

Von Neumann architecture sees and stores code as data
Harvard architecture stores data and code seperately
almost all general purpose architectures(x86,ARM,MIPS,PPC,SPARC,etc) -> Von Neumann


First documented worm = Morris Worm 
  -> stack buffer overflow in the fingerd service
  -> shut down the Internet
  
-> goal of the exploit is to launch a shell
